parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the headlights can cause accidents or leave the driver stranded, especially at night, and can lead to tickets or fines.
symptoms: Headlights turn off or dim while driving
sometimes one headlight and sometimes both
often without warning
and may come back on when the switch is turned off and on again.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake actuator can cause the brakes to malfunction, leading to accidents or loss of control, especially when driving on the highway.
symptoms: The brake pedal feels soft or spongy
the brake pedal sticks to the floor
the brake pedal does not return to its normal position
the brake pedal has a delayed return to its normal position
the brake pedal has a sudden loss of pressure
the vehicle is unable to stop or has reduced braking capability
loud noises or beeping sounds when braking
ABS and brake warning lights on the dashboard.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the combination meter can cause the dashboard lights to not illuminate, making it difficult or impossible to see important information such as speed, fuel level, and gear shift position, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The dashboard lights do not turn on
the speedometer does not work
the fuel gauge does not work
the gear shift indicator does not work
the engine warning lights do not work
the backup indicator beeper does not work.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the headlights can cause reduced visibility, making it difficult or impossible to drive safely, especially at night, which can lead to accidents.
symptoms: The headlights turn off intermittently
the headlights do not turn on
the headlights are dim or flickering.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brakes can cause loss of control of the vehicle, making it difficult or impossible to stop, which can lead to accidents.
symptoms: The brakes feel stiff or hard to press
the brakes do not respond
the brakes make a loud noise.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electrical system can cause various systems in the vehicle to malfunction, making it difficult or impossible to drive safely, which can lead to accidents.
symptoms: The vehicle's electrical system shuts down
the vehicle's systems malfunction
the vehicle's lights do not work.
